<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>A supplementary submission on the Committee on Climate Change’s (CCC)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">A supplementary submission on the Committee on Climate Change’s (CCC) </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">Fourth Carbon Budget Review – part 1, November 2</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">013</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">, and Cargo cult science</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">, Alex Henney</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“He who professes to foretell the future lies even if correct”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The Koran</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The CCC took no notice of the inaccuracy of the climate models</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> in AR5</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, which I set out in 2.2. of my main submission.  </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">The Independent of </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">20/3/00</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> reported that David Parker</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> of the Met Office’s </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Hadley Centre </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">forecast that “</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">British children could have only virtual experience of snow. Via the internet, they might wonder at polar scenes - or eventually "feel" virtual cold.</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">  This forecast was linked with that of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Dr David Vine</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">r of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the Climatic R</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">esearch </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">U</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">nit of the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">University</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">East Anglia</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">within a few years winter snowfall will become "</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">a very rare and exciting event" - </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">"Children just ar</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">en't going to know what snow is.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">"</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">In </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">2007, a</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> team of climate scientists from the Met Office wrote a paper “</span><a href="http://www.sciencemag.org/content/317/5839/796"><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:none">Improved Surface Temperature Prediction for the Coming Decade from a Global Climate Model</span></a><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">” </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">using their new modeling system </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">which forecast</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">There would be </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">0.3°C</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> warming over the decade 2004-2014</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:6.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">At least half of the years after 2009 would be warmer than the record year of 1998.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Ms.</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Vicky Pope</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> of the Met Office</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> gave a talk on these predictions, </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">stating t</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">hat</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“these are very strong statements about what will happen over the next 10 years.”</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">  </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">These predictions are wrong - there has been no warming at all since 2004; </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">none </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">of the years since 2009</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> h</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">ave broken the record of 1998 according to HADCRUT3 data</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Physics Nobel Prize Winner Richard Feynman’s inaugural lecture at Caltech in 1974 “Cargo cult science”</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> provides a useful concept.  If we were dealing with real science which hypothesizes then tests the hypothesis against reality, the abysmal record of the models in projecting/predicting/forecasting </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">(</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">or whatever word </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">one cares </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">to choose</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> would have led to chucking them out</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">and going back to the hypothesis drawing board. </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> The </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">Met Office would be eating humble pie for the aforementioned misforecast (and perhaps also for recent seasonal </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">mis</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">forecasts</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">).  But no, it is telling us the temperature pause is a temporary phenomena and normal warming will be continued soon in line with its </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">(CO2 </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">riven</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> models. We</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> are dealing with politicized and too often fanciful climate science whose models have in many</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">mind</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> become a pseudo reality – climate models are real cargo cult science.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">As Professor Richard Lindzen of MIT commented</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> in a seminar he gave in the House of Commons last year</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> “Climate science is immature.  It cannot forecast the past, let alone the future”.  And he commented of the Fifth Assessment Report</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">“I think that </span><a href="http://www.climatedepot.com/2013/09/27/45791/"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">the latest IPCC report</span></a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> has truly sunk to level of hilarious incoherence.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> They are proclaiming increased confidence in their models as the discrepancies between their models and observations increase…”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">All of CCC’s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> (and Met Office’s and IPCC’s) </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">talk of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">2</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">0</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">4</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:super">0</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">increases in temperature is </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">intellectual slop</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt"> (as is much else)</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">, and should be ignored</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><div style="width:auto; height:auto; float:left;"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1</span></p></div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">  Doug Smith, Steven Cusack, Andrew Colman,</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">Chris Folland, Glen Harris, James Murphy,  Science 10, August 2007, </span><a href="http://www.sciencemag.org/content/317/5839/796"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.sciencemag.org/content/317/5839/796</span></a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:9.75pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> The Met Office produced UK Climate Projections 2009 which purports to project “how the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> climate may change for the 30 year period from 2010-2099 at a resolution of 25km.” </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">limatologist </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">Professor Emeritus </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">R.A. Piel</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">ke Sr. of the </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">U</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">niversity</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">Colorado</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> in </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">Boulder</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">commented:-</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:9.75pt 0pt 9.75pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">This study…is clearly a subversion of the scientific method. To state that that climate science is being stretched is quite an understatement. There is absolutely no multi-decadal prediction skill on the spatial scales presented in this study.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:9.75pt 0pt 9.75pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold">The scientists who present the viewpoint of skillful multi-decadal regional predictions to policymakers are deliberately and dishonestly misinforming the public and policymakers.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">(emphasis original)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">See blog, A view of science worth reflec</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">ting on, 16/11, wattsupwiththat and Wikipedia cargo cult science.  Feynman commented:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">“</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">In the </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">South Seas</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> there is a cargo cult of people. During the war they saw airplanes land with lots of good materials, and they want the same thing to happen now. So they've arranged to imitate things like runways, to put fires along the sides of the runways, to make a wooden hut for a man to sit in, with two wooden pieces on his head like headphones and bars of bamboo sticking out like antennas--he's the controller--and they wait for the airplanes to land. They're doing everything right. The form is perfect. It looks exactly the way it looked before. But it doesn't work. No airplanes land. So I call these things cargo cult science, because they follow all the apparent precepts and forms of scientific investigation, but they're missing something essential, because the planes don't land.</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">Feynman cautioned that to avoid becoming cargo cult scientists, researchers must avoid fooling themselves, be willing to question and doubt</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">their own theories and their own results, and investigate possible flaws in a theory or an experiment. He recommended that researchers adopt an unusually high level of honesty</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">which is rarely encountered in everyday life</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">At a more modest scale, but apparently using similar models, the Met Office mis-forecast a “barbecue summer” for the washout in 2009; “milder-than-average winter” for 2010/11 through which we shivered; and a “drier-than-average” spring and early summer just before one of the wettest summers on record. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">“Global Warming: How to approach the science”, HoC, February 2012, </span><a href="http://scienceandpublicpolicy.org/images/stories/papers/reprint/how_to_approach_the_science.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">http://scienceandpublicpolicy.org/images/stories/papers/reprint/how_to_approach_the_science.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:9pt">.</span></p></body></html>